  "prompt_text": "Write a function to serialize and deserialize a binary tree. Explain your encoding scheme.",
  "response_text": "**Serialization and Deserialization of a Binary Tree**\n\nWe will use a pre-order traversal to serialize the binary tree. In pre-order traversal, we first visit the root node, then the left subtree, and finally the right subtree. This order allows us to uniquely represent the tree structure.\n\n**Encoding Scheme:**\n\n*   We will use a space-separated string to represent the serialized binary tree. The string will contain the node values in the order of pre-order traversal, followed by a special character to indicate the end of the left subtree, and another special character to indicate the end of the right subtree.\n*   We will use a comma (`,`) to separate the node values.\n*   We will use a `#` to indicate the end of the left subtree.\n*   We will use a `@` to indicate the end of the right subtree.\n\n**Serialization Function:**\n\n```python\nclass TreeNode:\n    def __init__(self, x):\n        self.val = x\n        self.left = None\n        self.right = None\n\ndef serialize(root):\n    \"\"\"\n    Serialize a binary tree into a string.\n\n    Args:\n        root (TreeNode): The root of the binary tree.\n\n    Returns:\n        str: The serialized binary tree.\n    \"\"\"\n    def preorder(node):\n        if node is None:\n            return '#'\n        return str(node.val) + ',' + preorder(node.left) + ',' + preorder(node.right)\n\n    return preorder(root)\n```\n\n**Deserialization Function:**\n\n```python\ndef deserialize(data):\n    \"\"\"\n    Deserialize a binary tree from a string.\n\n    Args:\n        data (str): The serialized binary tree.\n\n    Returns:\n        TreeNode: The root of the deserialized binary tree.\n    \"\"\"\n    nodes = data.split(',')\n    i = 0\n\n    def helper():\n        nonlocal i\n        if nodes[i] == '#':\n            i += 1\n            return None\n        node = TreeNode(int(nodes[i]))\n        i += 1\n        node.left = helper()\n        i += 1\n        node.right = helper()\n        return node\n\n    return helper()\n```\n\n**Example Usage:**\n\n```python\n# Create a binary tree:\n#       1\n#      / \\\n#     2   3\n#    / \\\n#   4   5\n\nroot = TreeNode(1)\nroot.left = TreeNode(2)\nroot.right = TreeNode(3)\nroot.left.left = TreeNode(4)\nroot.left.right = TreeNode(5)\n\n# Serialize the binary tree\nserialized_tree = serialize(root)\nprint(serialized_tree)  # Output: 1,2,4,#,#,5,#,#,3,#,#\n\n# Deserialize the binary tree\ndeserialized_root = deserialize(serialized_tree)\n```\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (",
